{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/shakey-2023","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I've used A* algorithm to search for the shortest path but I didn't know that it was created in the course of the Shakey project. Shakey the robot was able to reason about its own actions. This development dated back to 1968 😯</p>\n<p>Technically speaking I'm creating Shakey 2023. I plan to make it smaller.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/30d127228c0cc169ed3fb96e6ffaea6a/a-star-pathfinding.gif\" alt=\"a star pathfinding\"></p>\n<p>Here's a visualization of the training data. Graph in polar coordinates showing points that supposedly come from robot's sensors, as head rotation angle and distance approximation.</p>\n<p>Robot is in the center. Grid size is 5x5</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 332px; flex:0.9760479041916168;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/acd8028f1235b10166b141327cea7f39/71bac/next-step-training-data-polar.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 102.45398773006133%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"ANN training data to define the next step\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/acd8028f1235b10166b141327cea7f39/71bac/next-step-training-data-polar.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/acd8028f1235b10166b141327cea7f39/d2f63/next-step-training-data-polar.jpg 163w,\n/static/acd8028f1235b10166b141327cea7f39/c989d/next-step-training-data-polar.jpg 325w,\n/static/acd8028f1235b10166b141327cea7f39/71bac/next-step-training-data-polar.jpg 332w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 332px) 100vw, 332px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I think it might be quite interesting to compare the previous graph with how the points are located in the Cartesian coordinate system</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 445px; flex:1.0061728395061729;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/23c33a16808880d6e5c503b8053bbf12/e66bf/next-step-training-data-cartesian.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 99.38650306748465%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"ANN training data to define the next step - Cartesian coordinates\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/23c33a16808880d6e5c503b8053bbf12/e66bf/next-step-training-data-cartesian.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/23c33a16808880d6e5c503b8053bbf12/222b7/next-step-training-data-cartesian.png 163w,\n/static/23c33a16808880d6e5c503b8053bbf12/ff46a/next-step-training-data-cartesian.png 325w,\n/static/23c33a16808880d6e5c503b8053bbf12/e66bf/next-step-training-data-cartesian.png 445w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 445px) 100vw, 445px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Proper classification should predict the first move  based on the color of the dot as follows</p>\n<ul>\n<li>blue -> left</li>\n<li>purple -> up</li>\n<li>yellow -> right</li>\n<li>green -> down</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After robot makes the first move, it repeats the prediction</p>\n<p>Model for non-binary classification in Keras</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\">model <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> tf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>keras<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>models<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Sequential<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nmodel<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>add<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>tf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>keras<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>layers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Dense<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">32</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> input_shape<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> activation<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'tanh'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nmodel<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>add<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>tf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>keras<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>layers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Dense<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> activation<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'tanh'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nmodel<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>add<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>tf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>keras<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>layers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Dense<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">8</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> activation<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'tanh'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nmodel<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>add<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>tf<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>keras<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>layers<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Dense<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> activation<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'softmax'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\nmodel<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token builtin\">compile</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    optimizer<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'adam'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    loss<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'categorical_crossentropy'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    metrics<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token string\">'accuracy'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>So far this model gives very convincing result</p>\n<p>Notes: graph in the Cartesian coordinate system, distance and rotation normalized to [0, 1] interval</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 603px; flex:1.0382165605095541;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/65f94a758ecd19bcfb47a2fddfe84252/48d5f/next-step-model-prediction.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 96.31901840490798%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Prediction results\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/65f94a758ecd19bcfb47a2fddfe84252/48d5f/next-step-model-prediction.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/65f94a758ecd19bcfb47a2fddfe84252/d2f63/next-step-model-prediction.jpg 163w,\n/static/65f94a758ecd19bcfb47a2fddfe84252/c989d/next-step-model-prediction.jpg 325w,\n/static/65f94a758ecd19bcfb47a2fddfe84252/48d5f/next-step-model-prediction.jpg 603w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 603px) 100vw, 603px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Jupyter notebook link: <a href=\"https://github.com/mikolasan/ai_sandbox/blob/master/ann/Navigation%20ANN%20keras.ipynb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/mikolasan/ai_sandbox/blob/master/ann/Navigation%20ANN%20keras.ipynb</a></p>\n<p>Run Keras model and a web server in Python, get prediction using API from JavaScript.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/assets/84abb824a352df66588261255296317e/next-step-prediction-simulation.gif\" alt=\"using model in simulation\"></p>\n<p>Next step is macro behavioral model. We are going to use so called model free approach from [<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2211.10851.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Smart badger and Markov decision processes</a>] also leveraging physiological regulation.</p>\n<p>So we will create some sandbox with <a href=\"/ai/multi-agent-systems\">many independent agents</a> following the model. Just for fun, Lotka-Volterra model will be the first</p>","excerpt":"I've used A* algorithm to search for the shortest path but I didn't know that it was created in the course of the Shakey project. Shakey the…","tableOfContents":"","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/f0f0cf63-9b71-5c74-af40-d80dd2c1344c.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"March 04, 2023","published":"March 04, 2023","lastModified":"March 04, 2023","title":"Shakey 2023","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/shakey-2023.md","url":"/blog/shakey-2023","next":{"excerpt":"Previously I compiled TensorFlow 2.3 on Windows. This time I want to use a more powerful Linux workstation with an AMD graphics card. Thus I…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/build-rocm-from-source.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Build ROCM from source","date":"2023-04-22T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"d5369547-b655-5028-8925-f4a62c4ed145"},"previous":{"excerpt":"Last Sunday on a hike I was thinking if robots can love. I somehow came to that topic after reviewing associative memory and an ability of…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/blog/ai-analyzes-geopolitics.md","frontmatter":{"title":"AI analyzes geopolitics","date":"2023-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","topic":null,"article":null},"id":"eb1380eb-a3ff-56d4-bdf3-65ac7784aa34"},"recentArticles":[{"excerpt":"Trim video trim 3 seconds from start and 3 seconds from end. which means that from the total duration (this is how to check video length: 5…","fileAbsolutePa